  "latex": "\\sin 30° = \\frac{1}{2}, \\quad \\cos 30° = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}, \\quad \\tan 45° = 1",
  "explanation": "Memorize the special right triangles: 30-60-90 triangle has sides in ratio 1:√3:2, and 45-45-90 triangle has sides 1:1:√2. From these, you can instantly recall: sin 30° = 1/2, cos 30° = √3/2, sin 45° = cos 45° = √2/2, sin 60° = √3/2, cos 60° = 1/2. This saves time on exams and problem-solving.",
  "examples": [
    {
      "problem": "Find sin 30°",
      "solution": "1/2",
      "steps": [
        "30-60-90 triangle: sides 1, √3, 2",
        "sin = opposite/hypotenuse",
        "sin 30° = 1/2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "problem": "Find cos 45°",
      "solution": "√2/2",
      "steps": [
        "45-45-90 triangle: sides 1, 1, √2",
        "cos = adjacent/hypotenuse",
        "cos 45° = 1/√2 = √2/2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "problem": "Find tan 60°",
      "solution": "√3",
      "steps": [
        "30-60-90 triangle: sides 1, √3, 2",
        "tan = opposite/adjacent",
        "tan 60° = √3/1 = √3"
      ]
    }
  ],
